Name: UriToFile
Description: Download the specified Uri and output the file.
Result: Results are written to Console.Write(...)

Name: CsvToXml
Description: Convert a CSV into an Xml file.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .xml

Name: XmlToJson
Description: Convert an Xml file into a Json file.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .json

Name: JsonToJs
Description: Convert a Json file into a JS file.  Adds var filename = + json.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .js

Name: JsonToXml
Description: Convert a Json file to an Xml file.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .xml

Name: XsdFromXml
Description: Derive an Xsd from an Xml file.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .xsd

Name: XsltProc
Description: Process an Xml file given the specified Xslt file.
Result: Results are written to Console.Write(...)

Name: FileSetToFiles
Description: Extract the files (and their contents) from an Xml File Set.
Result: Results are created as multiple files as specified by the <RelativePath>...</RelativePath> fields of the FileSet.

Name: MSSQLDbToXml
Description: Extract an entire Database into a single XML file.
Result: Results are written to Console.Write(...)

Name: HtmlToXml
Description: Interpret html (liberally) to create a valid xhtml document.
Result: Results are written to Console.Write(...)

Name: XsdToOdxml
Description: Convert an XSD into an ODXML file, which powers the ODXML4 stack.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .odxml

Name: OdxmlToSqlSchema
Description: Converts an Odxml object model into a SQL script which will create that database structure
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .sql

Name: OdxmlToUpdateSqlSchema
Description: Convers an Odxml object model into a SQL script which will 'fill in the gaps' in a sql data model - if it already exists for the most part.  Tables will not be added.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .sql

Name: StaticDataToUpdateInsertSqlData
Description: Moves static data (from a spec doc set) into a sql data base created to match the structure
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .sql

Name: GetSqlSchema
Description: Connect to a SQL Server and extract the database objects as one, large xml document.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .xml

Name: SqlSchemaToOdxml
Description: Convert the Xml produced by the GetSqlSchema tool, into an Odxml object model.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .odxml

Name: MultiLinqualObjectListToResx
Description: Convert a list of objects (with multiple languages for DisplayName + Description, to create multiple language files (resx and cs)
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + ._multiple

Name: MultiLinqualPropertyListToResx
Description: Convert a list of object properties / attributes (with multiple languages for DisplayName + Description, to create multiple language files (resx and cs)
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + ._multiple

Name: MultiLinqualTokenListToResx
Description: Convert a list of tokens (with multiple languages for DisplayName + Description, to create multiple language files (resx and cs)
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + ._multiple

Name: OdxmlToOdxmlSubset
Description: Trim down an Odxml Data model to a much smaller list of objects and/or properties.
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .odxml

Name: OdxmlCleanup
Description: Applys a mapping from one odxml model to another
Result: Results are saved to a file with the same name as input file + .odxml
